Solution 1, by the AM-GM inequality:
$$\begin{array}{l}
\frac{a_{1}}{x_{1}}+\frac{a_{2}}{x_{2}}=\frac{a_{1}\left(x_{1}+x_{2}\right)}{x_{1}}+\frac{a_{2}\left(x_{1}+x_{2}\right)}{x_{2}}= \\
a_{1}+a_{2}+\frac{a_{1} x_{2}}{x_{1}}+\frac{a_{2} x_{1}}{x_{2}} \geqslant a_{1}+a_{2}+2 \sqrt{a_{1} a_{2}} \\
=\left(\sqrt{a_{1}}+\sqrt{a_{2}}\right)^{2}
\end{array}$$

where the equality holds if and only if:
$$\begin{array}{l}
\left\{\begin{array}{l}
\frac{a_{1} x_{2}}{x_{1}}=\frac{a_{2} x_{1}}{x_{2}} \\
x_{1}+x_{2}=1
\end{array}\right. \\
\left\{\begin{array}{l}
x_{1}=\frac{\sqrt{a_{1}}}{\sqrt{a_{1}}+\sqrt{a_{2}}} \\
x_{2}=\frac{\sqrt{a_{2}}}{\sqrt{a_{1}}+\sqrt{a_{2}}}
\end{array}\right.
\end{array}$$

Solution 2. By the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality:
$$\begin{array}{l}
\frac{a_{1}}{x_{1}}+\frac{a_{2}}{x_{2}} \\
=\left(x_{1}+x_{2}\right)\left(\frac{a_{1}}{x_{1}}+\frac{a_{2}}{x_{2}}\right) \\
\geqslant\left(\sqrt{x_{1}} \cdot \sqrt{\frac{a_{1}}{x_{1}}}+\sqrt{x_{2}} \cdot \sqrt{\frac{a_{2}}{x_{2}}}\right)^{2} \\
=\left(\sqrt{a_{1}}+\sqrt{a_{2}}\right)^{2}
\end{array}$$

